         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he is able to … from the Tuṣita-heaven</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>665</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he is able to lock up</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>665</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>128</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">he is able to (drive off) the ninety-eight kleśas (?)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>665</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">In one frame with <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht555"/>. 
The manuscript THT 522-557 consists of two layers of paper cut from a Chinese scroll. On this leaf, on one side only part of the Tocharian has been preserved (this part has not been edited in <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1953"/></bibl>, where only the "Rückseite" is given. To be consistent, this non-edited part is here given as recto side (even though on <bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/></bibl> the sides have been switched).</note></p>
         </div>
